The Lando thing wouldn't havr seemed skeevy and sexual if they had left in the part about him having a daughter who was kidnapped by the First Order. We think of it as sexual because there is no backstory, so the only reason he would ostenzibly be friendly with this stranger is because she's young and hot.

But had thry left in a passing line about his long lost daughter, we wouldn't have "hitting on her" in our minds in the first place. We'd be like "oh I get it; there's only like 3 black people in the galaxy so of course he would think she might be his daughter" lol

Just at least some reasonable setup to bring him back instead of pretending everyone forgotten he has died. And just it is redundant to make Rey a bloodlone of Palpatine if you want her to inherit the name of Skywalker and honor the legacy, Rian has already laid out the foundatiom that she is heir of nobody just like that child playing broomstick with foece at the end of TLJ. But they just have to fail the legacy in the more despicable way ever. How incompetence are they in planning a trilogy.
